Clear the terminal screen:
clear

See the location of the pointer:
pwd

Show contents of folder:
ls

Move up:
cd ..

Move to specefic folder:
cd folderName

Move ot root:
cd /

Show all files(also hidden):
ls -a

See all files also details:
ls -l

make a new directory:
mkdir directoryName

For delete:
rm -r directoryName 
rm nameOfFile   
rmdir directoryName

make a file:
touch f.txt

Open with an editor:
code f.txt 

see contents of a text file in the terminal :
cat f.txt

this helps when you need to look inside a small file.to see larger files use :
less f.txt

Renaming a file :
mv f.txt newName

copy a file :
cp newName.txt copied.txt

ocating a file/folder:
which fileName/foldername

see what commands you used upto 500 :
history

update Ubuntu :
sudo apt-get update

See network information :
ifconfig

ping a website :
ping google.com

see own os information :
uname -a

See system usage data :
top

See disk space :
df

Install software :
sudo apt-get install Name

Remove/uninsall :
sudo apt-get remove Name

Restart computer :
sudo reboot

Shutdown Computer : (try anyone)
sudo shutdown -h now
sudo poweroff
